    "updated_at": "2025-09-04T04:32:41Z",
    "body": "I notice if I have more sections (ruby via Gemfile, node via package.json, and Docker via Dockerfile) activated in my prompt, the more spaces are gone, though this only happen inside a terminal multiplexer like tmux/zellij session. this is my starship.toml\n\n```\nadd_newline = false\n\n[character]\nerror_symbol = \"[\\\\[▲\\\\]](bold bg:red fg:black) \"\nsuccess_symbol = \"[\\\\[I\\\\]](bold bg:green fg:black) \"\nvicmd_symbol = \"[\\\\[N\\\\]](bold bg:red fg:black) \"\n\n[cmd_duration]\ndisabled = true\n\n[custom.direnv]\nformat = \"[\\\\[direnv\\\\]]($style) \"\nignore_timeout = true\nstyle = \"fg:yellow dimmed\"\nwhen = \"env | grep -E '^DIRENV_DIFF='\"\n\n[hostname]\nformat = \"[$hostname]($style):\"\nssh_only = false\n\n[line_break]\ndisabled = true\n\n[nix_shell]\nimpure_msg = \"\"\n\n[username]\nformat = \"[$user]($style)@\"\nshow_always = true\n```\n\nEDIT: I also tested GNU screen, but weirdly, it appends more trailing spaces instead of removing them, like what happens in tmux/zellij",
